TITLE: Identifying Gaps in PostgreSQL Sequence IDs
DESCRIPTION: This SQL query identifies missing IDs in a sequence by comparing the range of IDs in a table against a generated series. It joins the table with a generated sequence spanning from the minimum to maximum ID value and returns records where the table ID is NULL, indicating a gap.
SOURCE: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/troubleshooting/why-are-there-gaps-in-my-postgres-id-sequence-Frifus.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT
    s.id AS missing_id
FROM
    generate_series((SELECT MIN(id) FROM your_table), (SELECT MAX(id) FROM your_table)) s(id)
    LEFT JOIN your_table ON your_table.id = s.id
WHERE
    your_table.id IS NULL;
```

