TITLE: Examining Query Plans to Determine Cost Thresholds in PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: Uses EXPLAIN to analyze the cost of two queries - a targeted index scan and a full table scan - to help determine an appropriate value for plan_filter.statement_cost_limit.
SOURCE: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/database/extensions/pg_plan_filter.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
explain select * from book where id =1;
                                QUERY PLAN
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Index Only Scan using book_pkey on book  (cost=0.28..2.49 rows=1 width=4)
   Index Cond: (id = 1)
(2 rows)

explain select * from book;
