TITLE: Creating a PostgreSQL function with JavaScript in PLV8
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a PostgreSQL function using JavaScript and the PLV8 extension. The function retrieves users who logged in within the last week using an external moment.js library.
SOURCE: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2021-05-03-supabase-beta-april-2021.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
create or replace function users_this_week()
returns json as $$
  const moment = require('https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/moment.js/2.29.1/moment.js', false);

  const lastWeek = moment().subtract(7, 'days');
  const query = 'select * from auth.users where created_at > $1'
  const users = sql(query, lastWeek);

  return users;
$$ language plv8;
```

