TITLE: Add Unique Numeric Key in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to add a new unique numeric key to a collection. It demonstrates modifying the document (`doc`) by adding a `unique_key` field derived from the `recordCounter` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/platform/migrating-to-supabase/firestore-data.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
module.exports = (collectionName, doc, recordCounters, writeRecord) => {
  doc.unique_key = recordCounter[collectionName] + 1
  return doc
}
```

