TITLE: Querying Auth Errors in SQL
DESCRIPTION: SQL query to find Auth-related errors by checking for 500 status codes and error/fatal level messages in the auth logs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/troubleshooting/resolving-500-status-authentication-errors-7bU5U8.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
select
  cast(metadata.timestamp as datetime) as timestamp,
  msg,
  event_message,
  status,
  path,
  level
from auth_logs
cross join unnest(metadata) as metadata
where
   -- find all errors
   status::INT = 500
    OR
  regexp_contains(level, 'error|fatal')
order by timestamp
```

