TITLE: Generating a Patch File for PostgreSQL Submission
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a formatted patch file from your commit. The format-patch command generates a file that can be attached to an email and sent to the PostgreSQL mailing list for review.
SOURCE: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2022-10-27-postgresql-commitfest.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
git format-patch -1 -v13

# 1   = patch depth.
#       The number of topmost patches to include
# v13 = the patch version.
#       Make new version number anytime you want to
#       send updated patch to the same thread)
```

